                <h1>Understanding Inclusion Background: Embracing Diversity</h1>
                <p>Inclusion background refers to the diverse social, cultural, and personal factors that shape individuals' experiences and identities. It emphasizes the importance of recognizing and valuing differences in race, ethnicity, gender, disability, and socioeconomic status, fostering a sense of belonging and equity in various settings.</p>
